asking these questions they need to bear in mind several factors. <#/>Firstly, as long as women are the gatherers of firewood, for lack of alternative energy fuel, the forests will continue to be destroyed and desertification will accelerate. <#/>Secondly
,
 as long as reafforestation and afforestation programmes are directed towards men, who are not the gatherers of wood for domestic consumption, deforestation will continue. <#/>Thirdly, as long as sound agricultural techniques and proper use of fertilizers
 
are taught to men or large plantation owners, soil depletion and poor land management will continue. <#/>This is coupled with the fact that most women do not have a registerable interest in the land that they till. <#/>Lastly, as long as the reproductive 
health of women is underemphasized, the health of their children will dete\-riorate. <#/>And, as population continues to grow, over-exploitation of existing natural resources will continue.
\par <#/>Bearing in mind that a majority of the women are either illitera
te or <-/semi-illiterate>, enacted policies or laws should make provision to ensure that these women fully understand and use them to advantage. <#/>Currently, the Agriculture Act, which provides the law for sound land management, is geared towards land o
w
ners, a majority of whom are men. <#/>As a result, women are left out or are unaware of the benefits that may arise under this Act. <#/>The Forest Act provides penal sanctions for those who flout the law but does no more. <#/>The result is that people wil
l continue to gather wood and destroy forests for lack of alternatives as long as they are not caught doing so.
